### Important: The Google Apps Script Code
To make this work, open a Google Sheet, go to **Extensions > Apps Script**, and paste this. Then Deploy it as a **Web App** with access to **"Anyone"**:

```javascript
function doPost(e) {
  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getActiveSheet();
  var data = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);

  // Append a row: Timestamp, Name, Email, Phone, Organization, Winner Status
  sheet.appendRow([
    data.timestamp,
    data.name,
    data.email,
    data.phone,
    data.organization || 'N/A',
    data.isWinner ? 'Winner' : 'No'
  ]);

  return ContentService.createTextOutput("Success").setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.TEXT);
}
```

Once you deploy that script, copy the **Web App URL** and paste it into `constants.ts`. Now, every time someone enters their details on their own phone, it will instantly appear as a new row in your central Google Sheet.

